spanGrp.span: In the old days when left, there was a lot of water
ases hed qay sing'eded qay beg asang' diya
'àsés héd qày sìng''édéd qày bég àsàng'' dìyà'
zamani tulipo toka maji yalikuwa ni mengi sana
In the old days in this field there was
jeed ab gilew senin qay gwand
jééd àb gílèw sénìn qày gwànd
zamani kwenye hiyo mbuga kulikuwa na
There were hippos and there were African buffalo, but today there is no water
gwand udomajega aa gwand muwak ased aa madgwand beg
gwànd údòmàjégà àà gwànd múwàk àsèd àà màdgwànd bég
kulikuwa na viboko na kulikuwa na nyati lakini leo hata maji hakuna
In the old days Mang'ola had a lot of trees, today there is no water
aa qay gedig aa sang' diya ab mang'ol ased beg aa mandan
'àà qày gédìg àà sàng'' dìyà àb màng''òl àséd bég àà màndàn'
'zamani mang''ola kulikuwa na miti mingi leo ha maji hakuna'
In the old days if we were farming
We were often farming rice, sorghum, and millet
gebaray mpunga gebaray mangure gebaray bukushid
gébàrày mpúngà gébàrày màngúré gébàrày búkúshìd
Because of the lack of water
kwa sababu ya ukosefu wa maji
This very day, the water in Mang'ola has become a problem, I mean everything
beg ased mandan ha mang'ol yani alanjed sen
'bég àséd màndàn hà màng''òl yàní àlànjéd sén'
'leo hii maji mang''ola imekuwa shida yaani vitu vyote'
All of them are gone, even those ones that I saw when I was small
sen gorota ar ga aday aa gatawas manang'
'sén gòròtá àr gà àdày àà gàtàwàs mänàng'''
vyote vimepotea hata yale niliyoyaona nikiwa mdogo
Today there isn't anything, everything is gone
leo hii hakuna vitu vyote vimepotea
Me, I don't know if it is because of development
anin aa manali ang'asheg maendelew gil
mimi sijua kama ni kwa ajili ya maendeleo
and what what it will be like, I don't know, even those things I saw when I was young, I don't see them today
aha gidwas anin aa manali alanjed gay aday aa gad dawas manang' ased madahi
'àhà gídwàs ànín àà mànàlí àlànjéd gày àdày àà gàd dàwàs mànàng'' àséd màdàhí'
na kitakachokuwa mimi sijui hata zile vitu nilivyoona udogoni leo hii sioni
Even corn is difficult to grow
ar boog geabarad kwa shida shida
àr bòòg géabàràd kwà shìdà shìdà
That is, just carelessly though, there isn't anything, they don't farm millet or sorghum
ha ab ha madaq gichay aa madgwand alanjed gorota mad ebar bukushi aa mad ebar mangur
hà àb hà màdàq gíchày àà màdgwànd àlànjéd gòròtà màd ébàr búkúshì àà màd ébàr màngúr
yaani tu kwa bure tu lakini hakuna tena vitu hawalimi tena ulezi wala mtama
Because of a lack of water
kwa sababu ya uhaba wa maji
Water isn't around anymore, only the water to be fetched in a gourd remains
beeg madgwand geaqusew beeg siram ba jeed qaded gichay
béég màdgwànd géaqúséw béég síràm bà jééd qàdéd gíchày
maji hakuna tena imebakia ya kuchotwa kwenye kibuyu
And if you get it, then you cook it
The field, if you farm you do one plot only, there isn't enough for two
ukwed ibar gibar safajand akalele mandangwand safajeg ijeny
úkwèd ìbàr gíbàr sàfàdʒànd àkàlélé màndàngwànd sàfàjég ìjény
shamba ukililima unalima safu moja tu hakuna cha safu mbili
We often grow only one plot
If you are lucky, then this is how it is
ha inyas bahat bas gwasina hay
hà ìnyàs bàhàt bàs gwàsínà hày
